description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trust Vision and Values are of great importance to us, we believe in demonstrating Respect, Responsibility, Honesty and Innovation in all aspects of our professional roles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Trust Vision is to always to ‘Deliver the Best in Care’ to all of our patients, visitors and service users. In order to ensure this we are constantly investing and developing our staff to discover new methods of care delivery, that are in line with evidence based practice, current research and the best outcome for all patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of this recruitment opportunity we are looking for Nurses and Operating Department Practitioners to join our theatre teams. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you want to work in a dynamic theatre setting? Where there are opportunities to develop your knowledge and skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have 74 theatres throughout the University Hospitals Birmingham, covering a wide range of specialties. There are excellent opportunities for successful applicants. We will encourage you to learn new skills and progress your theatre career. We cater for both elective and Emergency procedures; participate in Organ retrieval and transplantation as well as being a Major Trauma Centre. Our theatres are constantly expanding as the demand for our skills increases. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Within these theatres we have day case theatres covering many specialties such as Ophthalmic and Urology surgery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applicants must demonstrate within their application a strong commitment to teaching and desire to develop and progress your career within the Operating Theatre Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants are required to work a range of shifts which include earlies, late shifts, nights, weekends, long-day’s bank-holidays and on-calls.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you the person we are looking for?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information on these exciting opportunities then please contact: Melanie Finney.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Melanie.finney@uhb.nhs.uk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To apply for the position please complete the application form on NHS Jobs online.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
